                            <p>This is a letter from Edward O&#39;Farrell (1857-1926), the assistant under-secretary for Ireland, to Sir Charles Edward Troup (1857-1941), the permanent under-secretary of state  at the British Home Office. This letter was written a month following the Rising and relates to the enforcement of a state of martial law in Ireland. Enclosed is a written statement regarding martial law and a poster on same.</p>
                        
                    
                </note>
